  "prompt": "Where can I learn Tai-Chi in Bangalore?",
  "response": "Bangalore has several options for learning Tai-Chi. Here's a breakdown of places to look:\n\n**Established Tai-Chi Schools & Centers:**\n\n*   **Shambhala Wellness:** Offers regular Tai Chi classes with certified instructors. Look them up online or on Google Maps.\n\n*   **Art of Living:** While primarily known for yoga and meditation, Art of Living sometimes includes Tai Chi or related practices in their wellness programs. Check their course calendar.\n\n*   **Other Martial Arts & Wellness Studios:** Many martial arts schools or wellness centers may offer Tai Chi as one of their disciplines. Search online for \"martial arts Bangalore\" or \"wellness centers Bangalore\" and then check their course listings.\n\n**Finding Independent Instructors & Group Classes:**\n\n*   **Online Directories & Platforms:**\n    *   **Justdial:** Search for \"Tai Chi classes in Bangalore\" on Justdial.\n    *   **UrbanPro:** This platform connects students with tutors and instructors. Search for Tai Chi teachers in your area.\n    *   **BookMyShow:** Sometimes, BookMyShow lists wellness workshops, including Tai Chi.\n    *   **Google Search:** A simple Google search like \"Tai Chi classes Bangalore near me\" or \"Tai Chi instructors Bangalore\" can yield good results.  Look closely at the search results; some might be forum discussions or blog posts listing instructors.\n\n*   **Community Centers & Parks:**\n    *   **Check with local community centers or parks.** Sometimes, they host Tai Chi groups or instructors who teach at a low cost.\n    *   **Observe groups in parks:** Keep an eye out for groups practicing Tai Chi in parks. Ask them if they are open to new members.\n\n**Tips for Choosing a Tai-Chi Class:**\n\n*   **Style of Tai-Chi:** There are different styles of Tai-Chi (Yang, Chen, Wu, Sun being the most common). Research the styles and see which one resonates with you. Many instructors will specialize in one style.\n*   **Instructor Credentials:** Look for instructors with certifications or significant experience in Tai Chi. Ask about their training background.\n*   **Trial Class:** If possible, attend a trial class before committing to a longer course. This will allow you to assess the instructor's teaching style and the class environment.\n*   **Location and Schedule:** Consider the location and schedule of the classes to ensure they fit your lifestyle.\n*   **Reviews and Recommendations:** Read online reviews or ask for recommendations from friends or family who practice Tai-Chi.\n*   **Cost:** Inquire about the fees for the classes or workshops.\n\n**When searching, be specific with your location within Bangalore.**  Bangalore is a large city.  Searching for \"Tai Chi classes near [your specific neighborhood]\" will give you more relevant results.\n\nGood luck in your search!\n",
